# Copy this file to  scripts/blocked-terms.local  (git-ignored) and add
# case-insensitive extended-regex patterns for your environment/company
# identifiers — account nicknames, SSO role names, internal product/cluster
# names — that must never be committed to this public repo. The pre-commit hook
# (scan-account-data.sh) reads blocked-terms.local and blocks any staged content
# that matches. One pattern per line; text after '#' is a comment.
#
# blocked-terms.local is git-ignored on purpose: the sensitive terms live only on
# your machine, never in the repo. CI never sees the file, so this is a LOCAL
# guard layered on top of the always-on account-id / secret / hash scan.
#
# Keep patterns PRECISE so they don't collide with generic English. Do NOT add a
# bare word like "harness" or "traceable": those appear in normal prose
# ("test harness", "traceable to evidence") and would flag legitimate content.
# Anchor to the distinguishing form instead.
#
# Illustrative fictional examples (replace with your own in blocked-terms.local):
# acme-prod-[a-z0-9-]+
# acme\.internal
# acme-readonly-role
# \bAcmeWidgets\b
